==English==

===Pronunciation===
*flūtter /flʌɾŗ/
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ʌtə(r)|-ʌtə(r)]]
===Verb===
'''to flutter'''
# (''intransitive'') to [[flap]] or [[wave]] [[quickly]] but [[irregularly]]
# (''intransitive'') (''of a bird or insect'') to flap the [[wing]]s without [[flying]]; to [[fly]] with a light flapping of the wings
# (''transitive'') to cause something to flutter

====Translations====
'''to flap or wave quickly''' (1)
*Finnish: [[lepattaa]]
*French: [[voleter]], [[voltiger]]

'''to flap the wings without flying''' (2)
*Finnish: [[räpyttää]]

'''to cause something to flutter''' (3)
*Finnish: [[väpättää]]

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''flutter'''
# the act of [[fluttering]]
# a state of [[agitation]]
# an [[abnormal]] rapid [[pulsation]] of the [[heart]]
#(''British'') a small [[bet]]
